{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Weigh 150 g carrots slices and broccoli florets in Varoma dish.","Insert Varoma tray in Varoma dish, line Varoma tray with baking paper and arrange salmon fillets on Varoma tray. Season with 1 pinch salt and ground pepper, spread 1 tsp tikka paste on top of each salmon fillet and set Varoma aside.","Place lentils, lemon zest and ginger into mixing bowl, chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Chop again <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add 300 g carrots chunks, onions, garlic, and butter, chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water, stock paste, ½-1 tsp salt and 1 pinch pepper, place Varoma into position and steam <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep warm.","Add coriander and milk and blend soup <b>1 min\/speed 5<b><strong>-10, increasing speed gradually<\/strong>. Serve the soup hot, garnished with some coriander leaves and a swirl of cream. Garnish the salmon tikka with remaining coriander leaves, finely cut, and serve with steamed vegetables on side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["450 g carrots, 150 g cut into slices (approx. |5 mm) and 300 g cut into chunks","200 g broccoli florets","4 fresh salmon fillets (150-180 g each)","½ - 1 tsp salt, plus extra to taste","2 pinches freshly ground black pepper","4 tsp tikka paste","50 g red lentils","½ lemon, zest only","2 cm fresh ginger, sliced","100 g onions, cut into quarters","1 garlic clove","50 g butter, cut in pieces","700 g water","1 heaped tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","2 sprigs fresh coriander, plus some extra leaves to garnish","100 g milk","4 tsp cream, to garnish (optional)"]}],"id":"r168164","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-voERnwOozTE\/XZapf9TT7zI\/AAAAAAAAhRU\/fejmE2ToVjoB2RU00GTEjAKcyknoTEVSQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_03PkPUk2lAnub5IX.png","title":"Carrot coriander soup and tikka salmon with steamed vegetables","published